author: breser
msg: Make fs_fs properly cleanup after a failed transmission of a representation.
In particular it's valid for a client to resend a failed PUT via DAV and
continue with the activity/transaction (e.g. after a read error).  However,
fs_fs would never remove its being_written flag and would leave the partial
This particular problem is not seen by our client implementation since
upon the first error we stop sending the commit and DELETE the
Resolve the problem by setting a pool cleanup function to detect when this
occurs and truncate the protorevfile to remove the broken representation and
(rep_write_cleanup): New function to revert a rep that wasn't not completed.
(rep_write_get_baton): Set the rep_write_cleanup callback to the baton pool.
(rep_write_contents_close): Remove the rep_write_cleanup once the rep has
successfully been written to the file but before we add the node.
